n<li id=\"cite_note-Martin-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-Martin_5-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Martin_5-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Martin_5-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Gregory Martin, <i>The Flemish School, 1600-1900</i>, National Gallery Catalogues<i>, 1970, National Gallery, London, <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-901791-02-4\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-901791-02-4\">0-901791-02-4</a></i></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Grove-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-Grove_6-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Grove_6-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Grove Art online, accessed May 12, 2007</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Ingamells, John, <i>The Wallace Collection, Catalogue of Pictures, Vol IV, Dutch and Flemish</i>, Wallace Collection, 1992, <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-900785-37-3\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-900785-37-3\">0-900785-37-3</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-rkd-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-rkd_8-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://rkd.nl/explore/artists/32262\">Abraham Godijn</a> at the <a href=\"/wiki/Netherlands_Institute_for_Art_History\" title=\"Netherlands Institute for Art History\">Netherlands Institute for Art History</a> <span class=\"languageicon\">(in Dutch)</span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw1328\nCached time: 20180910020753\nCa